──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 1 — Healy CFF Cadence (P1)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ORGAN     : System/swarm_cff_cadence.py
PAPER     : Healy et al. 2013
MATH      : log10(CFF) = α + β · log10(metabolic_rate) − γ · log10(body_mass)
            (refit from Healy Table 1; intercepts species-specific)
            Tunable via env: SIFTA_SPECIES ∈ {human,hummingbird,dog,
            leatherback,fly}. Default human.
PROOF     : assert that hummingbird preset → CFF >= 75 Hz, leatherback
            preset → CFF <= 20 Hz, present_window = 3/CFF, integrates
            with swarm_default_mode_network refresh rate.
ECONOMY   : higher CFF burns more inference per wall-second
            (more polls/s × sample cost). Costs scale linearly. The
            STGM bill of being a hummingbird is real.
RUBRIC    : +5 visible to Alice in composite_identity ("My CFF is X Hz
            so my present moment is Y ms wide.") | +10 actually changes
            asyncio sleep cadence | +5 STGM-metered

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 2 — Pacemaker-Accumulator Interval Timer (P2, P5)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ORGAN     : System/swarm_pacemaker_accumulator.py
PAPER     : Buhusi & Meck 2005; Gibbon 1977
MATH      : pulses_per_sec = λ_pacemaker · (1 + dopamine_modulation)
            estimate(Δt) ~ Normal(μ=Δt, σ=CV·Δt), CV=0.20
            elapsed_estimate(t_now − t_anchor) returns biological estimate
PROOF     : run 1000 trials of estimate(60s); assert
            E[estimate]≈60s and Std[estimate] ≈ 12s (CV=0.20 ±0.05).
            Show scalar property holds at 5/30/300/1800s.
ECONOMY   : free to read; fee on registering a new anchor (memory cost)
RUBRIC    : +10 scalar property empirically demonstrated | +5 visible
            to Alice ("I think we last spoke about 8 minutes ago,
            give or take 90 seconds")

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 3 — Striatal Beat-Frequency Clock (P2, P6)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ORGAN     : System/swarm_striatal_beat_clock.py
PAPER     : Matell & Meck 2004
MATH      : N=64 oscillators with f_i ~ uniform(8, 13) Hz (theta range)
            phase_i(t) = (2π · f_i · t) mod 2π
            coincidence(t) = Σ cos(phase_i(t))   # peaks when in phase
            criterion-pattern memory: Hebbian weights w_ij learned from
            "this is what coincidence looked like at t=criterion".
            Recall: weight × coincidence dot product crosses threshold.
PROOF     : train on 4s criterion, test on 0–10s sweep, peak response
            within ±0.4s of 4s (Weber 0.10).
ECONOMY   : training a new criterion costs STGM (memory consolidation)
RUBRIC    : +10 peak within Weber tolerance | +5 dual-criterion (4s and
            7s) without interference | +5 visible to Alice

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 4 — Pöppel Subjective Present Window (P4)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ORGAN     : System/swarm_subjective_present.py
PAPER     : Pöppel; White 2017 critical revision
MATH      : present_window_s = base_window · (60 / cff_hz)
                       · (1 + density_modifier(events_per_sec))
            base_window = 3.0 (Pöppel) for human-CFF; White's
            information-density modifier shrinks it under high event
            rate.  Replaces SIFTA_DIALOGUE_CONTEXT_WINDOW_S magic 600.
PROOF     : at human-CFF + low density → ~3s window. At hummingbird-CFF
            → <1s. At high density (10 events/s) → halves. Integration
            test: replaces _gather_state(window_s) with this organ's
            output and the 8 sample greetings still parse.
ECONOMY   : free
RUBRIC    : +5 retires the magic 600s constant | +5 species-tunable
            | +5 visible to Alice

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 5 — Dopamine→Clock Modulator Bridge (P2)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ORGAN     : System/swarm_dopamine_clock_bridge.py
PAPER     : Buhusi & Meck 2005, §"Pharmacology"
MATH      : reads endocrine_glands.jsonl current_dopamine ∈ [0,1]
            modulator = 1 + α · (dopamine − dopamine_baseline)
            α from Meck 1996 amphetamine studies (~0.3 per σ DA).
            Exposes get_clock_rate_modulator() consumed by Event 2 and
            Event 1 organs.
PROOF     : assert HIGH-DA preset → pacemaker emits ≥30% more pulses/s
            than baseline; LOW-DA preset → ≤−30% (Parkinsonian regime).
            Integration test: a 60s wall-clock interval estimated
            during HIGH-DA returns Mean ≤ 50s ("time flew"), during
            LOW-DA returns Mean ≥ 80s ("time crawled").
ECONOMY   : free (it's a bridge, not a producer)
RUBRIC    : +10 Meck pharmacology effect reproduced in silico
            | +5 visible to Alice ("I have a lot of dopamine right now,
            so this conversation feels like it's flying by")

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EVENT 6 — Cross-Species Time Persona (P1, P4)
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ORGAN     : System/swarm_species_time_persona.py
PAPER     : Healy 2013 + Pöppel 1997
MATH      : preset table from §2 cross-species card. Setting
            SIFTA_SPECIES rewrites: CFF → cadence, present_window,
            scalar CV, memory-density dilation slope. Single switch,
